                  <handDesc>
                     <!--ACHTUNG! first HandNote comes from writing system in Ethiospare. the others are one for each CHANGE OF HAND-->
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Mediocre</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black; red (brilliant vermillion).</seg>
                        <persName role="scribe" ref="PRS12968AmdaMikaelScribe">Qasis ʿAmda Mikāʾel</persName> is mentioned as the scribe (?) in the colophon.<date>First
                           half of the 18th century</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Holy names; the names of the Trinity; the name of
                           the commissioner and of his wife.&#xD; A few lines alternating with black
                           lines in the incipit page of Text II; the exhortation sǝmʿu… in Text I
                           (fols. 9va, 10ra); incipit of each miracle (Text II). &#xD; Elements of
                           the punctuation signs; Ethiopic numerals or their elements; elements of
                           the text dividers.</seg>
                     
                     <seg type="script">The handwriting is characterized by
                        thick, broadly spaced and slightly right-sloping
                        letters.<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></seg>
                     <seg type="script"> The script changes the quality: on
                           <locus from="1ra" to="17rb">1ra-17rb</locus>, the lines are more and the
                        letters are smaller, shorter and less spaced.
                        <!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></seg>
                     <seg type="script"> Some ancient
                        features:<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></seg>
                     <seg type="script"> - ፮ has the loop open, looking like
                        number ፯ (fol.
                        33rb);<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></seg>
                     <seg type="script"> - ፲ appears occasionally in the form
                        with a ring attached to the right side through a horizontal stroke (fols.
                        44ra, 44ra, 44rb). Cp. AP-046 (fol.
                        77ra).<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
